modules.description: This module implements runtime support for assertion checks in test cases, providing functions to validate predicates, compare values for equality, and report mismatches. It operates on values of arbitrary type `'a`, using S-expressions for serialization and comparison. These functions are used to enforce correctness in test suites by checking expected outcomes against actual results, with optional custom equality and diff reporting.

This module provides runtime utilities for validating assertions in tests, supporting predicate checks, value comparisons, and structured reporting of mismatches. It works with values of any type `'a`, using S-expressions for serialization and customizable equality checks. Developers can assert that expressions evaluate to expected values, compare complex data structures, and generate detailed diffs when comparisons fail. For example, one can write an assertion that a computed list matches an expected list, with a custom printer to format elements for clearer failure messages.
